I had a dream this morning that I was at my grandparent's house, which is in the country, with William Moseley (Chronicles of Narnia). We were riding bikes extremely fast and we stopped at this old house. We wandered around for a bit and then we sat down, and were talking (about Ghost Hunters) and just as I was about to kiss him (>.>), Jorge Garcia walked in. He walked around a little and we scattered. Then William Moseley said something like, "We weren't up to what you think we were up to," to which I muttered a bitter, "Unfortunately, not yet."

Today was my last final exam! I read a ridiculous but funny story about a woman who was set on shooting a tiger, but ended up shooting the bait, aka the goat, and the poor tiger died of a heart attack from the sound. That was my dramatic speech, and now all my classes are over! A quick sort of sketch I did today of Frodo. Title: Frodo Baggins Rating: G Medium: pencil
